item.title: How do i put training in edge?
item.dc:creator: @ChemicalReaction1 ChemicalReaction™
item.description:
@ChemicalReaction1 wrote:

Go to client.java and search ( Ctrl+f )

newObject

Now you should see some stuff there.
it would say something like

AddGlobalObject

Copy and paste one of those lines. and add it to the top
the first+second numbers are coordinates ( I just told you about them )
3rd number is object ID ( dummy is 823 )
4 th is Which way the object is facing.

item.title: How do i put training in edge?
item.dc:creator: @ChemicalReaction1 ChemicalReaction™
item.description:
@ChemicalReaction1 wrote:

ok you know where you start.
stand on that “EXACT” Spot. and type ::coordson and 8 yellow numbers seperated by , will apear in the corner , They are coordinates…
now go to your server file and open up to file named “server” and press Ctrl+F and type in the first 4 numbers that appeared when you typed ::coordson .
now go to where you want the starting place to be. and look at the numbers again. and type in the first 4 numbers in CoordX and the 2nd 4 numbers in CoordY.
Im not explaining anymore. that is very noob friendly.
